      "text": [
        " «تَتَّزِرُ بِإِزَارٍ إِلَى اَلرُّكْبَتَيْنِ وَ تُخْرِجُ سُرَّتَهَا ثُمَّ لَهُ مَا فَوْقَ اَلْإِزَارِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.204 - Ubaidullah ibn Ali Al-Halabi asked Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) about what is permissible for a husband with regard to his menstruating wife.\nImam (as) said: 'She should cover herself with a cloth (izar) from her navel to her knees, and he may have what is above the izar.'."
        ]
      }
